ose fled with the SS men. Now . . ."},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2422.018","u": "The capos, who had a good conscience, who had been behaving fair towards their fellow prisoners, they stayed with us and also celebrated their freedom."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2430.777","u": "Yes. Now. Eh&#226;did one catch some SS men? Did one . . ."},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2436.340","u": "Very many were still caught on the way because . . . many inmates took eh, plundered right away these weapons arsenals, the arsenals of the SS . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2446.486","u": "Yes . . ."},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2447.044","u": ". . . and armed themselves and those strong enough ran after the SS, together with the Americans. Quite a few were still arrested."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2455.049","u": "And what was done to them?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2456.315","u": "They were first brought into the camp, and held in a block. They were disarmed and everything taken from them. Then, several days later, they were transported by the Americans, by the military, into Germany."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2469.853","u": "Did you have the opportunity to talk to the SS?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2473.468","u": "I did not have the opportunity myself because the whole time I was to weak to just go few steps out."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2479.378","u": "Well."},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2479.845","u": "I had to strenthen myself first."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2481.926","u": "But others did?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2483.660","u": "Yes, but I just rested. Others had the opportunity to talk to the SS men. Many also took revenge."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2492.781","u": "In what form?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2494.062","u": "Simply by harrassing them."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2496.776","u": "Yes. Did the Americanse defend or protect the SS in any form?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2503.846","u": "Neither defended nor protected them. They took&#226;in the first days you saw rather few Americans in our camp because the camp was still in the front line, the whole area. Only later when the front had moved further into Germany, came a special camp commando of the U.S. Army, a great number of personnel, who took over the order of the camp. Also many tankers came that brought water into the camp. Because it took about a a week and a half until the water pipeline was restored."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2538.724","u": "Aha. Now tell me, there were so many inmates, how come that the SS was even left alive?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2549.792","u": "They were left alive. Because if we would not have left them live, the we would, we would not have been much different than the Germans. So we had to, we wanted to, after all, be a good example, if not by good example, but we should not have done to them what they did to us, then we would have been just the same."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2568.485","u": "That was the philosophy?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2571.229","u": "That was not the philosophy, that is my opinion. Surely many others had another opinion. But overall that was the mindset in the camp."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2578.924","u": "Is it true, that inmates hanged SS men in Buchenwald?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2583.974","u": "Inmates hanged SS men?"},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2585.813","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2586.477","u": "That happened twice as far as I know."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2588.542","u": "Yes. When?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2589.115","u": "That was then&#226;after the liberation."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2591.407","u": "Yes?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2591.995","u": "Those were indeed SS men who had just acted especially atrociously towards the inmates. But I only heard of it so I cannot tell more details about it."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2603.889","u": "You did not see that yourself?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2605.367","u": "No."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2605.834","u": "No. Now, and how did it go with food and meals?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2609.694","u": "Of course, the food improved immediately and immensely. Many were not used to the good fare of the American military, in fact, no one was . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2619.990","u": "Yes ."},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2620.503","u": ". . . many suffered right away from diarrhea, stomach aches, gastritis. Nobody took well to it. The whole camp suffered from diarrhea. And only later, slowly, slowly, did we get used the the normal diet."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2633.882","u": "Now, and how long were you then in Buchenwald?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2637.093","u": "I was then in Buchenwald until the beginning of June 1945, when many youths had to had to sign up through the U.N. [?] and the transports went to Switzerland, and I was among them. And so I came to Switzerland."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2652.500","u": "You chose Switzerland?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2654.520","u": "Yes."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2654.912","u": "Have you tried to find your family or anybody?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2658.123","u": "I already did enough research. But I have no hope that anyone of them stayed alive. I only found my aunt and my uncle in Chile again who had emigrated there before&#226;during the war."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2672.445","u": "What are their names?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2673.425","u": "Dahlinger."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2674.495","u": "Dahlinger. And how did you find them? Did you write them, and did they answer?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2680.737","u": "I did research through the Red Cross and several other organizations, and one, then one message came from them. And in September of last year I had the first message from them."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2691.606","u": "Aha. And, eh, what are you doing now?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2696.400","u": "Momentarily I am learning to be a dental technician in a laboratory of the OSE and besides I am taking evening classes at the commercial school, learning English, French, and . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2704.601","u": "What commercial school?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2706.666","u": "The Institute Commercial here in Bern."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2709.078","u": "Is that a private school?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2710.465","u": "No, that is a state school."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2711.732","u": "And you are allowed to attend the -?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2713.737","u": "I was allowed to attend the school, the OSE that also finances dental technician training, allowed me to attend this course and finances this also."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2722.149","u": ". . . and finances this course. And how do you get along with your co-students?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2727.757","u": "I, I had, I have not been long in this course, just a couple of days because the winter semester has just begun . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2733.953","u": "Yes . . ."},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2734.571","u": ". . . and I did not really have nearer contact with my fellow students yet, but it is going well."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2739.214","u": "Aha. Did they know that you, eh, were a former prisoner?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2744.099","u": "I think, I don&#39;t know. They did not say anything, anyway."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2746.707","u": "And how old are you now?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2748.004","u": "I will be 18."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2749.708","u": "And what are your plans? What do you want to do in the future?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2752.979","u": "I am intending to finish the dental technician course and the evening course at the commercial school, and then go to my relatives in Chile and work there as a dental technician."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2762.356","u": "Don&#39;t you want to study dentistry?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2765.070","u": "I don&#39;t think I will have an opportunity to study dentistry because that requires the Maturit&#195;t [general qualification for university entrance]. I am already too old and . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2773.588","u": ". . . too old . . . ?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2774.568","u": "Not too old, but I just don&#39;t have enough time anymore to prepare for that."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2779.679","u": "Well now, you are just a single person. You could maybe earn some money and work towards the Maturit&#195;t, no?"},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2786.870","u": "I never had an opportunity to earn something, and I would not know as what or how."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2790.594","u": "Aha. Now, Gert, that was a very comprehensive report. I have heard some things from you that I had not heard from others, because I [interviewed] very few German prisoners. You also described things very intelligently. I am convinced that it is a good report, that I may play for certain German groups in Chicago. I am convinced that they will&#226;I cannot say, they will be happy, but very satisfied to learn of this. Many thanks."},    {"who": "Gert Silberbart", "start": "2830.729","u": "You are welcome . . ."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2831.368","u": "[In English] This concludes the report with Gert Silberbart at, eh, about seven minutes of Spool 83. Paris, August the 27th 1946. In a home supported by the Swiss government for refugees of the war. Illinois Institute of Technology wire recording."},    {"who": "David Boder", "start": "2864.280","u": "This concludes the reproduction of Spool 9-83, the interviewee was Silberbart. The sign-off gave by mistake Paris, it really was in Geneva but somehow the interviewer automatically having interviewed people for a number of days in Paris still gave the sign-off as Paris. It is Geneva . . . Switzerland. November the 14th, 1950, Chicago, of course. Boder."}        ]
    }
_jsready = true;
var return_val;
switch (String(type)){
        case "transcription":
        return_val = transcription.interview;
        break;
            case "english_translation":
        return_val = english_translation.interview;
        break;
    }
return return_val;
}
function js_ready(){
    return _jsready;
}
